-- Bank of America to pay $16.6 mln to resolve U.S. sanctions violations 
-- By Aruna Viswanatha
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 10:15AM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, July 24 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp's banking unit <BAC.N> agreed to pay $16.6 million to resolve allegations that it processed transactions for drug traffickers who are subject to U.S. sanctions, the U.S. Treasury Department said on Thursday.

